text: Satterthwaite is a village and civil parish in South Lakeland, Cumbria, England. In 2001 there were 257 people living in Satterthwaite. It has 9 listed buildings. It has a church called All Saints which has 4 stained glass windows. == References == Category:Villages in Cumbria Category:Civil parishes in Cumbria
